Sentencas: On the basis of the one-dimensional, isothermal mechanistic model in the anode of an anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell using binary mixture as fuel, two approximate analytical solutions considering both mass and charge transfer were developed in this article.
Titulo: An approximate analytical solution of transport model in electrodes for anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: First, by dividing the anode into the inactive and active zones, the regular perturbation method was used to approximate the distribution of the fuel concentration and overpotential.
Titulo: An approximate analytical solution of transport model in electrodes for anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Then the approximate solution using the singular perturbation method reflects both the boundary-layer effects of current density at the two boundaries of the anode.
Titulo: An approximate analytical solution of transport model in electrodes for anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Both the two approximate solutions agree, well with the numeric solution in the case of medium and low electric load.
Titulo: An approximate analytical solution of transport model in electrodes for anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: By introducing the concept of the boundary-layer thickness at the anode/electrolyte interface, the two approximate solutions can be combined to get an explicit expression in a wide range of operation.
Titulo: An approximate analytical solution of transport model in electrodes for anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The result in this article is useful to system-level modeling anti dynamic analysis.
Titulo: An approximate analytical solution of transport model in electrodes for anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells
